---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout>
    <section class="pt-24 pb-16 px-6 bg-white min-h-screen">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-[#423c3b] mb-6 leading-tight">
                Geoglyphs of Nasca and Palpa
            </h1>
            <img src="/geoglifos2.webp" alt="Geoglifos de Nasca y Palpa" class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-lg mb-8" />

            <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 text-lg">
                <p>
                    Explore the magic of the desert and the mystery of ancestral lines on a comprehensive tour that combines strategic viewpoints with history, science, and culture.
                </p>

                <p>
                    This tour includes:
                </p>

                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-binoculars mr-2 text-[#a59f89]"></i>
                            Nasca Metallic Viewpoint:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            Located next to the Pan-American Highway, this metal-framed viewpoint allows you to clearly observe three iconic figures: Las Manos (The Hands), El √Årbol (The Tree), and part of El Lagarto (The Lizard). A must-see for those who want to appreciate the lines up close and take excellent photographs.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-mountain mr-2 text-[#a59f89]"></i>
                            Nasca Natural Viewpoint:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            From a natural rocky elevation in the desert, you'll have a breathtaking panoramic view of the traces and the surrounding landscape. A perfect place to experience the magnitude and mystery of these ancient creations.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-university mr-2 text-[#a59f89]"></i>
                            Maria Reiche Museum:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            Located in what was once the home of the renowned German researcher, this small but valuable museum immerses you in the life and legacy of the woman who dedicated decades to studying and preserving the Nazca Lines. You'll see her measuring instruments, original maps, and personal belongings.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#423c3b]">
                            <i class="fas fa-eye mr-2 text-[#a59f89]"></i>
                            Palpa Viewpoint:
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            At this stop, you'll be able to observe some of the oldest geoglyphs in the region, such as the Royal Family and other unique humanoid figures from the Paracas culture. A different perspective enriches the experience and reveals the diversity of the valley's geoglyphs.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-base pt-4">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Tour duration:</strong> Approximately 3 to 3.5 hours
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Departure from:</strong> City of Nasca
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Includes:</strong> Tourist transportation from Nazca, Admission to all viewpoints and the museum, Specialized local guide, Rest and photo stops.
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <div class="pt-4">
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold">
                        <i class="fas fa-sun mr-2 text-[#a59f89]"></i>
                        Recommendations:
                    </h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-base">
                        <li>Bring sunscreen, water, a hat, and sunglasses.</li>
                        <li>Comfortable clothing and suitable footwear for walking.</li>
                        <li>Camera.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <p class="pt-2">
                    Live a unique experience in the Peruvian desert and connect with one of the greatest enigmas of the ancient world. Book your tour today!
                </p>

                <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mt-10">
                    <a href="/#tours" class="text-[#423c3b] px-6 py-3 rounded-lg border border-[#423c3b] text-base font-medium hover:bg-[#423c3b] hover:text-[#cbc4ae] transition">
                        <i class="fas fa-arrow-left mr-2"></i> Back to Itineraries
                    </a>
                    <a href="https://wa.link/0voy2n" class="bg-[#423c3b] text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg text-base font-medium hover:bg-[#3d3433] transition" target="_blank">
                        <i class="fa-brands fa-whatsapp"></i>
                        Request Reservation
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
